      Platform

      NanoOne - a platform technology

      The NanoOne platform is the fastest high-resolution 3D printing system available. It combines the precision of 2-photon polymerization with unmatched high throughput.

      Areas of application

      The versatility and performance of UpNano printing systems enable entirely new applications possibilities, setting new standards in manufacturing.

      NanoOne 250

      This entry model is a printing system with enhanced speed for all classic 2PP applications.

      NanoOne 1000

      The NanoOne 1000 has the most powerful femtosecond laser in its class.

      NanoOne bio

      NanoOne bio allows 3D printing of structures in the presence of living cells for biological applications with unprecedented precisions.

Application areas

The fast-paced world we live in demands increasingly smaller, more powerful products and components, all while development cycles grow shorter. This poses a challenge for traditional, often tool-based manufacturing technologies. However, industries and research facilities worldwide are seeking new, innovative, and industry-ready solutions to keep up. Solutions that, thanks to 2PP 3D printing, are now within reach.

Roche

Dr. Mike Nikolaev

Postdoctoral Researcher, Bioengineering

“Using NanoOne, we have reduced the production time for a microfluidic chip from many hours on our in-house tool to just minutes.”

“The exceptional combination of high laser power, fine resolution and intuitive software was instrumental in achieving this remarkable speed boost. NanoOne has become an indispensable instrument, playing a pivotal role in numerous research projects at the Roche Institute of Human Biology. It greatly facilitates the prototyping of new microfluidic chips and the bioengineering of next-generation organ-on-chip models for various R&D projects at Roche. Looking ahead, we’re already exploring avenues to further expand our capacity, and we’re confident that we have the ideal partner by our side.”

Read more Collapse

3D printers

Introducing a revolutionary printing platform merging additive manufacturing flexibility with industrial production demands. Based on multiphoton lithography, this versatile technology allows for the manufacturing of highest precision components with structural details as small as 150 nm and macroscopic microparts in the centimeter range, empowering users to create nano- and microstructured parts across various sectors. Dive into the future of micro-manufacturing with UpNano’s user-friendly, fast process.

Shape accuracy and tolerances

of less than 1 µm

Highly reproducible process

with over 96% yield

Optical surface finish

in the two-digit nm range

Industry-proven production process

without post-treatment

Software

Discover the seamless integration of hardware, resin, and software with the proprietary user software Think3D. It’s the all-in-one solution for reproducible and high-quality 3D printing operations. Developed by users, Think3D prioritizes intuitiveness and remote accessibility. With features like adaptive resolution, subjob printing, autofocus, and real-time data processing, Think3D elevates your 3D printing experience to a new level, enabling unprecedented manufacturing approaches.

Operating software

A streamlined and intuitive process for cost-efficiency and high-quality parts.

Subjobs

Unprecedented precision and efficiency are achieved with Think3D’s revolutionary subjob feature.

Well plate dock

Parameter definition and creation of gradients have never been so easy, straight forward, and intuitive.

Learn more

Resins

UpNano offers a portfolio of high-performance 2-photon resins optimized to fully exploit the capabilities of ultrafast high-resolution printing systems like NanoOne. With nine resins tailored for specific applications, ranging from performance photopolymers to optically transparent materials for optical and microfluidic applications, to biocompatible formulations tested for in-vitro cytotoxicity according to EN ISO 10993-5:2009, these materials provide unmatched versatility and performance.
